Sirs: I=92m following up on BG Cox=92 report below, which summarizes yester=
day=92s planning meeting at 3rd RGMT=92s drill. I can add the following det=
ails for other parts of TNMAN:

  *   JBAT Mission: I have 3 POCs: MAJ Garner, CPT Gray, and CPT Kasinger. =
They will report by tonight the # PAX, names, and MRC for participating SMs=
. MAJ Garner and CPT Kasinger are traveling but they will update the tracki=
ng spreadsheet at the Google address below. At this time we are relying on =
TDOT for signal.
  *   Mapping mission is staffed and briefed by TEMA. TNSG=92s participatio=
n is primarily signal with 2PAX (MAJ Wemyss and 1SG Wade). MAJ Wemyss will =
lead Starlink and Field CP capability at Fall Creek Falls, arriving on 12MA=
Y (Tuesday) early and heading home 13MAY. Chief Simpson and 1SG Wade will p=
rovide additional support. Drone participation will be MTSU aerospace drone=
 pilots, up to 5. They will be working directly with TEMA, and sending sign=
al through us. We=92ll have Starlink capability to send images, but no HF s=
upport as that is not part of that exercise.
  *   Cyber mission is staffed by 3 PAX (Chief Barbas, LT Mule, and CPT Lac=
ey); Chief Simpson is also listed on their mission but I anticipate he will=
 not be active with that team and will instead monitor remotely. That missi=
on occurs in one day, 14MAY (Thursday).
  *   Mt. Carmel site defense mission is below. We are tracking 31PAX in th=
at mission at this time. In addition to BG Cox=92 notes you can see LTC She=
af=92s planning on the spreadsheet - he=92s set the standard for tracking O=
ps over time. In addition, LT Overton=92s planning portal app can be seen a=
t https://tnman-2026.web.app<https://tnman-2026.web.app/>. You can see deta=
ils by signing in with your TNSG email address (by name). Troops arrive 13M=
AY, with most activities on 14MAY. We are flexible on ENDEX, anticipating i=
t on evening of 14MAY but able to support if it extends into the morning of=
 15MAY. I=92m coordinating with G6 for frequencies for HF. 3rd RGMT will st=
and up the HF antenna and we=92ll test propagation throughout the day. We=
=92ll also have a Starlink on site there as part of the PACE plan.
  *   HHC LNOs: we are tracking 5PAX (Hughes, Barbas, Coulter, Jernigan, an=
d Hogan) at this time. The busy day will be 14MAY. Hogan will be receiving =
PERSTATs throughout the day.

Additional items:

  *   Chief Hogan is tracking HHC participation under COL Ritter=92s leader=
ship.
  *   Staffing the JOC at Sidco will occur with LNOs and TNSG leadership at=
 the table behind the desks in the JOC.
  *   OICs for TNSG are in direct contact with their TDOT and TEMA counterp=
arts, and are updating me with details as they come available.
  *   FRAGO will be published with updated info this week.
  *   I need to confirm with 61st MedCo for personnel to be located for Map=
ping, Cyber, and Sidco.
  *   I need frequencies for the HF for TNMAN.

More info later this week.

V/R

LTC Estes


