<div>
<div style=3D"line-break:after-white-space">Sirs: I=92m following up on BG =
Cox=92 report below, which summarizes yesterday=92s planning meeting at 3rd=
 RGMT=92s drill. I can add the following details for other parts of TNMAN:
<div>
<ul class=3D"x_MailOutline">
<li><b>JBAT Mission</b>: I have 3 POCs: MAJ Garner, CPT Gray, and CPT Kasin=
ger. They will report by tonight the # PAX, names, and MRC for participatin=
g SMs. MAJ Garner and CPT Kasinger are traveling but they will update the t=
racking spreadsheet at the Google
 address below. At this time we are relying on TDOT for signal.</li><li><b>=
Mapping</b> mission is staffed and briefed by TEMA. TNSG=92s participation =
is primarily signal with 2PAX (MAJ Wemyss and 1SG Wade). MAJ Wemyss will le=
ad Starlink and Field CP capability at Fall Creek Falls, arriving on 12MAY =
(Tuesday) early and heading
 home 13MAY. Chief Simpson and 1SG Wade will provide additional support. Dr=
one participation will be MTSU aerospace drone pilots, up to 5. They will b=
e working directly with TEMA, and sending signal through us. We=92ll have S=
tarlink capability to send images,
 but no HF support as that is not part of that exercise.</li><li><b>Cyber <=
/b>mission is staffed by 3 PAX (Chief Barbas, LT Mule, and CPT Lacey); Chie=
f Simpson is also listed on their mission but I anticipate he will not be a=
ctive with that team and will instead monitor remotely. That mission occurs=
 in one day, 14MAY
 (Thursday).</li><li><b>Mt. Carmel site defense mission</b>&nbsp;is below. =
We are tracking 31PAX in that mission at this time. In addition to BG Cox=
=92 notes you can see LTC Sheaf=92s planning on the spreadsheet - he=92s se=
t the standard for tracking Ops over time. In addition, LT Overton=92s
 planning portal app can be seen at&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://tnman-2026.web.=
app/">https://tnman-2026.web.app</a>. You can see details by signing in wit=
h your TNSG email address (by name). Troops arrive 13MAY, with most activit=
ies on 14MAY. We are flexible on ENDEX,
 anticipating it on evening of 14MAY but able to support if it extends into=
 the morning of 15MAY. I=92m coordinating with G6 for frequencies for HF. 3=
rd RGMT will stand up the HF antenna and we=92ll test propagation throughou=
t the day. We=92ll also have a Starlink
 on site there as part of the PACE plan.</li><li><b>HHC LNOs:</b>&nbsp;we a=
re tracking 5PAX (Hughes, Barbas, Coulter, Jernigan, and Hogan) at this tim=
e. The busy day will be 14MAY. Hogan will be receiving PERSTATs throughout =
the day.</li></ul>
<div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div><b>Additional items:</b></div>
<div>
<ul class=3D"x_MailOutline">
<li><b>Chief Hogan is tracking HHC participation</b> under COL Ritter=92s l=
eadership.</li><li><b>Staffing the JOC at Sidco</b> will occur with LNOs an=
d TNSG leadership at the table behind the desks in the JOC.</li><li><b>OICs=
</b> for TNSG are in direct contact with their TDOT and TEMA counterparts, =
and are updating me with details as they come available.</li><li><b>FRAGO</=
b> will be published with updated info this week.</li><li>I need to confirm=
 with <b>61st MedCo </b>for personnel to be located for Mapping, Cyber, and=
 Sidco.</li><li>I need <b>frequencies</b> for the HF for TNMAN.</li></ul>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>More info later this week.&nbsp;</div>
